<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="137" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="38.[212,1444,1202,1607]" pageId="38" pageNumber="137">
DESCRIPTION. — Pale grey, densely squamose. Elytra in either sex with two tubercles at end of dorsum, a prominent one on interstria 3, a small one on 5, this a little basad from that on 3; elytral dorsum in lateral view in female rather strongly convex (much as in 
<taxonomicName box="[519,629,1272,1296]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Elytrogonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="labrami">
<emphasis box="[519,629,1272,1296]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="137">H. labrami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[212,1444,1202,1607]" pageId="38" pageNumber="137">Male: tergite 7 truncate. Sternite 9 robust, strongly curved, ending in a large, broad expansion. Aedeagal body about 1.3 x longer than apodemes, rather strongly curved, blunt at apex, shallowly emarginated at base; flagellum shorter than aedeagal body, robust, with a heavily pigmented base, reinforced and wider at basal 1/4, from here on half the basal thickness.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[212,1444,1202,1607]" pageId="38" pageNumber="137">Female: sternite 8 rather broadly rounded at apex, medially strongly pigmented, briefly bifurcate, rather densely setose; apodeme unusually robust, especially near blade. Distal hemisternites parallel-sided, with apical margin below styli at about right angle to axis, with a distinct emargination. Spermathecal duct extension curving strongly away from stem; stem reinforced to a knob, conically extended towards a cylindrical gland.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[212,1444,1202,1607]" box="[242,458,1583,1607]" pageId="38" pageNumber="137">Length: 6.2-8.0 mm.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
